tasks.details:
The implementation uses a Cloudflare Worker located at `functions/circuit-breaker/index.ts`. It reads the `weekly_spend_usd` and `weekly_cap_usd` values from a Cloudflare KV store named `BUDGET_KV`. This worker acts as a middleware for the AI proxy. If the spend exceeds the cap, the worker returns a '503 Service Unavailable' error to halt further processing and prevent additional costs.

Pseudo-code for the worker:
```typescript
// In functions/circuit-breaker/index.ts
export default {
  async fetch(request, env, ctx) {
    const weeklySpend = await env.BUDGET_KV.get('weekly_spend_usd') || 0;
    const weeklyCap = await env.BUDGET_KV.get('weekly_cap_usd') || 100;

    if (parseFloat(weeklySpend) >= parseFloat(weeklyCap)) {
      return new Response('Budget exceeded. Service temporarily unavailable.', { status: 503 });
    }
    // If budget is okay, the request proceeds to the main AI proxy.
  }
}
```
